# Chrome Extension

The Biasbuster Chrome extension allows users to analyze web content directly from their browser.

## Key Components

- **manifest.json** - Extension configuration file
  - [chrome-extension/manifest.json](mdc:chrome-extension/manifest.json)

- **Content Scripts** - Scripts that run in the context of web pages
  - [chrome-extension/content_scripts/content.js](mdc:chrome-extension/content_scripts/content.js)
  - Extracts article content and sends to Biasbuster API

- **Popup UI** - User interface when clicking the extension icon
  - [chrome-extension/popup/popup.html](mdc:chrome-extension/popup/popup.html)
  - [chrome-extension/popup/popup.js](mdc:chrome-extension/popup/popup.js)
  - Provides analysis controls and displays results

## Installation

1. Open Chrome and navigate to `chrome://extensions/`
2. Enable "Developer mode"
3. Click "Load unpacked" and select the `chrome-extension` directory
